comments: As they approach the pick, Smart (BOS) and Allen (CLE) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Allen (CLE) rolls to the basket and incidental foot to foot contact occurs with Schroder (BOS) as he moves alongside him.
Tatum (BOS) avoids contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm on his dislodge attempt during the post shot.
Before the pick, Osman (CLE) and Langford (BOS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Rubio (CLE) cleanly pokes the ball loose and any follow-through contact to Schroder's (BOS) arm after the dislodge is deemed incidental.
After the dislodge, Rubio (CLE) briefly grasps and immediately releases Schroder's (BOS) arm and marginal contact occurs as they both pursue the loose ball.
The ball is cleanly dislodged by Rubio (CLE) and Schroder (BOS) does not have control of the ball when he touches it after the dislodge and before it rolls into the backcourt.
Mobley (CLE) makes contact with Tatum's (BOS) arm, which affects his jump shot attempt.
The 24 second shot clock expires before the ball goes out of bounds and a shot clock violation is correctly whistled.
After the pick, Tatum (BOS) and Mobley (CLE) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) avoids making contact with Mobley's (CLE) arm during his contest on the jump shot attempt.
During the pick, Osman (CLE) and Langford (BOS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Langford (BOS) firms up on his right foot in Mobley's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs as he engages on the pick.

The contact between Osman (CLE) and Tatum (BOS) as Osman attempts to establish himself in a legal guarding position in Tatum's path is marginal.  Tatum does not dislodge him from his defensive position.
Williams III (BOS) is deemed to be in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Allen (CLE) firms up on his right foot and marginal contact occurs with Smart (BOS) as he slightly extends his hips during the screen.

Smart (BOS) initially makes clean ball contact when he reaches across Garland's (CLE) body, but Garland is still able to gather and then Smart makes contact with his arm and pulls his hand off the ball, which affects his driving shot attempt.
During the screen, Valentine (CLE) and Schroder (BOS) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Osman (CLE) moves alongside Schroder (BOS) and any marginal contact is created by Schroder slightly extending his arm out.
Osman (CLE) legally contests Schroder's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
Williams III (BOS) and Allen (CLE) both extend their arms up to pursue the rebound and any contact is deemed incidental.
